+ 1. PIPELINE

--- OBJECTIVE 
! We will go through 4 steps of the pipeline to grab, enrich and generate a enriched breadcrumb for a website made with the CLMS wordpress. I works for tags and categories bu I will focus on tags.

! STEP_1: connect Python to a WordPress MySQL DB, fetch all tags and categories with post counts, export to CSV. Covers `001_step_1_list_tags_categories_wp.py`.

! STEP_2: run spaCy NER on taxonomy terms, detect entity types (ORG, PERSON, GPE, PRODUCT…), understand what your tags actually mean semantically. Covers `002_step_2_spacy_ner.py`.

! STEP_3: query Wikidata API to attach canonical IDs, labels, and descriptions to each term. Why knowledge graphs matter for SEO. Covers `003_step_3_wikidata_enrich.py`.

! STEP_4: write enriched proposals to custom tables, validate state machine (pending → approved → published), JSON breadcrumb array structure. Covers `004_step_4_breadcrumb_proposal.py` and `create_tables.sql`.

